    Cited by: 16 articles Refresh citation count Citing literature

Abstract

[1]  Aggressive measures were instituted by the Beijing municipal authorities to restrict vehicular traffic in the Chinese capital during the recent Sino-African Summit. We show that reductions in associated emissions of NO x were detected by the Dutch-Finnish Ozone Monitoring Instrument (OMI) aboard the Aura satellite. Interpretation of these data using a 3-dimensional chemical transport model indicates that emissions of NO x were reduced by 40% over the period of November 4 to 6, 2006, for which the restrictions were in place.
Continue reading full article

